      "size_string": "sizeof(s_widget_animation_collection_definition)",
      "flags": 736,
      "fields": [
        {
          "type": "explanation",
          "name": "Animations",
          "definition": "Ambient-Focused: Plays when the widget is idle, and has focus\nAmbient-Unfocused: Plays when the widget is idle, and does not have focus\nAmbient-Disabled-Focused: Plays when the widget is idle, disabled, and has focus\nAmbient-Disabled-Unfocused: Plays when the widget is idle, disabled, and does not have focus\nTransition-From: Plays when transitioning away from the screen, going forward\nTransition-To: Plays when transitioning into the screen, going forward\nTransition-Back-From: Plays when transitioning away from the screen, going backward\nTransition-Back-To: Plays when transitioning into the screen, going backward\nCycle In Previous Pane: Plays when a screen transitions in by cycling in from left\nCycle In Next Pane: Plays when a screen transitions in by cycling in from the right\nCycle Out Previous Pane: Plays when a screen transitions in by cycling out to the left\nCycle Out Next Pane: Plays when a screen transitions in by cycling in out to the right\nList Group Transition In: Plays when a list display group transitions in\nList Group Transition Out: Plays when a list display group transitions out\nControl Receive Focus: Plays when a control receives focus\nControl Lost Focus: Plays when a control receives focus\nIndicator Ambient Additional Items: Plays when control is idle and has more items in the indicator's direction\nIndicator Ambient No Additional Items: Plays when a control is idle and has no more items in the indicator's direction\nIndicator Activated Additional Items: Plays when a control is activated in the indicator's direction and there are more items in that direction\nIndicator Activated No Additional Items: Plays when a control is activated in the indicator's direction and there are no more items in that direction\nLoad Submenu (focused/unfocused): Plays for list when it invokes a submenu\nUnload Submenu (focused/unfocused): Plays for a list when it is restored by dismissing a submenu\nLoad As Submenu: Plays for a list when it is invoked as a submenu\nUnload as Submenu: Plays for a submenu list when it is disposed to return to its top-level menu\nChild Submenu (focused/unfocused): Plays for a list when it has a child submenu active after transitioning\n"
        },
